data.name: radioButton_db_fix_on.ToolTip
data.value:
In math and physics, 0 input is not possible when db measurement is taken.
This option will enable a simple fix for songs/tracks 0 samples by replacing each sample with input 0 with input of 1 bit which is 1.
This make the song/track feels alive also correct in math/physics.
This will replace 0 sample into 1 bit sample, so it will be ~ 0,00305 % level of amplitude instead of 0. AND: 0 db instead of infinity db. This is correct.

data.name: radioButton_wave_fix_shift.ToolTip
data.value:
Shift wave form to make sure all samples are above 0.
This will make audio correct physically if it is enabled with DB fix, all samples will be above 0. If it is not, 0 would exist in the wave form (in the middle) and this would be impossible physically (infinity db) so it will destroy the sound when listnening in real live. This option attempts to fix that.
